OL,3,CGulls, Greggs and guinea fowl:
OL,4,CStudents' wild excuses for being late
OL,5,Cto school
OL,7,FThe Education Secretary has said there
OL,8,Fis an "absence epidemic" in schools,
OL,9,FRhys Williams reports
OL,11,FChildren often come up with the most
OL,12,Fcreative excuses for being late to
OL,13,Fschool, with a new study revealing
OL,14,Fthat seagulls, Greggs, and guinea fowl
OL,15,Fhave all been blamed.
OL,17,FA survey by the research app Teacher
OL,18,FTapp, involving over 2,000 teachers,
OL,19,Ffound that rather than the usual "the
OL,20,Fdog ate my homework" excuses, seagulls
OL,21,Fwere blamed for tardiness 18 times.
